sections.History:
=== [[Season 3]] ===
When [[Locke]] was about to let his men rape Brienne, [[Jaime Lannister]] told him who she was and that Tarth was called the &quot;Sapphire Isle&quot; because every sapphire in the [[Seven Kingdoms]] was mined on it, to point out the wealth of her father. Locke relents and orders his men not to harm Brienne, as it would be more worthwhile to ransom her unharmed.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Brienne later pointed out that the &quot;Sapphire Isle&quot; is actually so-called because of the blue of its waters: there are no actual sapphire mines on the island.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
